### Test Authentication Flow for ET-Ticket API
### Make sure the server is running on http://localhost:4000

### 1. Health Check
GET http://localhost:4000/api

### 2. Request OTP for User (B2C - Mobile)
POST http://localhost:4000/api/auth/otp/request
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "+251911223344"
}

###

### 3. Verify OTP and Login/Register User
### NOTE: Check server console for the OTP code
POST http://localhost:4000/api/auth/otp/verify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "+251911223344",
  "otp": "255795"
}

###

### 4. Register Organizer (B2B - Web)
POST http://localhost:4000/api/auth/organizer/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "+251922334455",
  "email": "organizer@example.com",
  "name": "Test Organizer"
}

###

### 5. Request OTP for Organizer (Should get "Pending Approval")
POST http://localhost:4000/api/auth/otp/request
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "+251922334455"
}
### 6. Verify OTP for Organizer (Should fail with "Pending Approval")
POST http://localhost:4000/api/auth/otp/verify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "+251922334455",
  "otp": "REPLACE_WITH_OTP_FROM_CONSOLE"
}
### 7. Test Protected Route (Replace TOKEN with accessToken from step 3)
GET http://localhost:4000/api/protected
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

### 8. Refresh Token
POST http://localhost:4000/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}

###
